The paper discusses the design and deployment of the wireless control plane (WCP) in 5G networks, which involves managing heterogeneous wireless devices and access technologies. This topic falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI) and systems and control (cs.SY). The paper also proposes a framework for WCP design using deep reinforcement learning (DRL), which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper discusses the intricacies of WCP design, which involves addressing security concerns (cs.CR) and optimizing network performance (cs.IT).
